24 SECTION 7. ORS 656.252 is amended to read:
25 656.252. (1) In order to ensure the prompt and correct reporting and payment of compensation
26 in compensable injuries, the Director of the Department of Consumer and Business Services shall
27 make rules governing audits of medical service bills and reports by attending and consulting physi-
28 cians and other personnel of all medical information relevant to the determination of a claim to the
29 injured worker’s representative, the worker’s employer, the employer’s insurer and the Department
30 of Consumer and Business Services. Such rules shall include, but not necessarily be limited to:
31 (a) Requiring attending physicians [and nurse practitioners authorized to provide compensable
32 medical services under ORS 656.245] to make the insurer or self-insured employer a first report of
33 injury within 72 hours after the first service rendered.
