10 ORS 654.001 to 654.295, 654.412 to 654.423, 654.750 to 654.780 and this chapter. To that end the di-
11 rector may:
12 (a) Make and declare all rules and issue orders which are reasonably required in the perform-
13 ance of the director’s duties. Unless otherwise specified by law, all reports, claims or other docu-
14 ments shall be deemed timely provided to the director or board if mailed by regular mail or
15 delivered within the time required by law. Notwithstanding any other provision of this chapter, the
16 director may adopt rules to allow for the electronic transmission and filing of reports, claims or
17 other documents required to be filed under this chapter and to require the electronic transmission
18 and filing of proof of coverage required under ORS 656.419, 656.423 and 656.427. Notwithstanding
19 ORS 183.310 to 183.410, if a matter comes before the director that is not addressed by rule and the
